TITLE: Performing One-Time Queries with Algolia Helper
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the searchOnce method for one-time queries that don't affect the helper's state, useful for fetching specific results without changing the main search parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/packages/algoliasearch-helper/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var state = helper.searchOnce(
  { hitsPerPage: 1 },
  function (error, content, state) {
    // if an error occured it will be passed in error, otherwise its value is null
    // content contains the results formatted as a SearchResults
    // state is the instance of SearchParameters used for this search
  }
);
```

