TITLE: Incorrect Post-Interaction Testing in InstantSearch Tests (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Example of incorrect testing after user interaction using a full snapshot, which doesn't clearly show what changed as a result of the interaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#2025-04-17_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const showMoreButton = container.querySelector('.ais-RefinementList-showMore');

userEvent.click(showMoreButton);

// Don't use a snapshot to assert the whole HTML structure after an interaction
// as they're harder to read and don't help focusing on what has changed.
expect(container).toMatchInlineSnapshot(`
  <div>
    <!-- … -->
  </div>
`);
```
